Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 12 MRSA ยง6502-C, sub-ยง2-C is enacted to read:
3 2-C. Commercial license; island communities. Notwithstanding subsection 1-B, the
4 commissioner shall allocate one commercial menhaden fishing license for each of the
5 following island communities to be issued to an applicant who is a resident of each
6 community:
7 A. Chebeague Island;
8 B. Cliff Island;
9 C. Frenchboro;
10 D. Great Cranberry Island;
11 E. Isle au Haut;
12 F. Islesboro;
13 G. Islesford;
14 H. Long Island in Casco Bay;
15 I. Matinicus Isle;
16 J. Monhegan;
17 K. North Haven;
18 L. Peaks Island;
19 M. Swan's Island; and
20 N. Vinalhaven.
21 A license issued pursuant to this subsection may not be transferred to a resident of an island
22 community other than the community to which the commissioner allocated the license. If
23 a license that is allocated for an island community goes unissued for 3 consecutive years,
24 the commissioner may reallocate that license to another community listed under this
25 subsection.
26 The commissioner shall work with the municipal officers of the island communities listed
27 under this subsection and with relevant local organizations within those communities to
28 implement and administer this subsection, including verifying applicant residency,
29 facilitating the allocation of licenses and identifying the need for additional licenses to be
30 issued as incentives to attract year-round residents.
31 SUMMARY
3322 This bill directs the Commissioner of Marine Resources to allocate one commercial
3333 menhaden fishing license each for certain island communities to be issued to an applicant
3344 who is a resident of each community. The bill prohibits a license issued to a resident of an
3355 island community from being transferred to a resident of a community other than the
3366 community to which the commissioner allocated the license. The bill also allows the
3377 commissioner to reallocate a license that goes unissued for 3 consecutive years to another
3388 island community and directs the commissioner to work with the municipal officers of the
Page 1 - 132LR2010(01)

319 island communities and relevant organizations within the communities to implement and
420 administer the provisions of the bill.
